ion into electrons of 6%. The electron spectra generated by the\nDLA-mechanism in NCD-plasma at 1019 Wcm-2 laser intensity were compared with\nthose measured in shots onto conventional metallic foils at ultra-relativistic\nlaser intensities of 1021 Wcm-2 . In the last case, the twice lower effective\nelectron temperature and the twice lower maximum of the electron energy were\nregistered. The substantial difference in the electron spectra for these two\ncases presented itself in the isotope production yield.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 May 2020 13:18:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-01"}
